07/04/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Council of Europe Parliamentary Assembly (COEPA) President Peter Schieder expressed optimism Tuesday (6 April) about Turkey's ability to implement EU-oriented legislative reforms. 
In a speech at the opening of the COEPA Chairmanship Council meeting in Istanbul, Schieder said that in its efforts to speed up the process of acquiring EU membership, Turkey is trying to implement in two years reforms that usually take about a decade.
In other news, Azerbaijan on Tuesday warned Turkey against opening its border with Armenia. 
Azerbaijan has a longstanding territorial dispute with Armenia over the Baku region. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV, trend - 06/04/04)
